Volcano GlovesThe Volcano Gloves from REV'IT! are the lightest ADV gloves in the REV'IT! collection with CE certification. Designed with a mix of on-road and off-road use in mind, the Volcano Gloves are more robust than a full dirt glove and feature a fortified microfiber synthetic palm. Air mesh on the back of hand keeps the hands cool and dry during high effort maneuvers. TPR knuckle sliders with Seesoft viscoelastic backing add protection. Temperfoam can be found again at the palm and thumb. A hook and loop closure keeps the gloves secure, and an oversized pull loop makes for easy entry. fix up.name: 2008 Honda Odyssey EX-L
fix up.description: I bought this Odyssey from a neighbor who was the original owner a couple years ago or so. He is an orchid grower and used it to transport his plants all over the state (mostly freeway miles).  I fixed a few small problems and it's been a solid reliable vehicle for us. It's also an extra vehicle, (we've driven it under 2000 miles in 2 years) and as nice as it was to have it, we don't need it. So time to move it on.Recent repairs/////In the last 2000 miles are-Valve Cover Gaskets (because they were leaking) and Valve Adjustment and new Spark Plugs at that time -Front Axles-Air & Cabin Filters-Transmission drain & fill-Installed a Blue Tooth / phone setup//////In the last 10,000 miles/////-Front Brake Pads and Rotors-Right Rear Wheel Bearing////////////////////////////////////////////The Timing Belt & Water Pump, Bearings + Tensioner were replaced at 115,000 in 2002 (Original Honda Parts) Rear Brakes are better than 50% leftMichelin Tires have about 40% or so leftThe right rear corner has got dinged a couple times (by a couple different people) it's not bad tried to show it. famous.name: Famous FS-1 Soprano Ukulele OBO
famous.description: Pretty little soprano, nice build with super-thin mahogany laminate, but with a sound that will rival most sold-wood ukes. Extremely light, with excellent projection and beautiful resonance. The FS-1 is a Japanese build, identical to the Kiwaya KS-1, but sold only to the Japanese market. This older uke has a Rosewood fingerboard, which you won't find in production any longer...the newer ones are walnut.  Nice, low action and great intonation. Friction tuners. Tiny scratch on the headstock, mark on the first fret - see the photos for detail. One-of-a-kind cloth gig bag included. Reasonable offers are welcome.

famous.name: gladiator guitar and peavey amp
famous.description: DescriptionThis Gladiator Vintage Series is designed to be an accurate reproduction of a famous Vintage masterpiece, in all of its dimensions, finish colors and tonal characteristics. The authentically contoured body is of American Ash and the bolt-on neck is a solid piece of Canadian maple, which incorporates the 12-fret fingerboard with its abalone position dots. The vintage-style 'skunk stripe' is inlaid in the back of the neck. Two powerful Wilkinson® single-coil ceramic pickups with Alnico magnets combine with a 3-way switch for a variety of authentic tones. The traditional stamped-steel bridge with 3 saddles is pure vintage, and the small-button, enclosed tuning machines are period correct.The GL-221-VGR is finished in Vintage Green with a 3-ply laminated ABS pickguard of mint green.American Ash bodyCanadian maple 1-piec neck and fingerboard with vintage-style skunk stripe & Abalone position markersMulti-ply Mint/Black/Mint pickguardWilkinson® 1950s inspired alnico magnet single-coil pickups with 3-position pickup selector switchTraditional chrome-plated stamped-steel bridge with 3 vintage-style chrome-plated saddlesAuthentic nickel-plated, small-button, closed-back tuning machinesAdjustable truss rod25 1/2scale lengthBone nutChrome-plated neck pickup cover and control plateVintage GreenPeavey BACKSTAGE 2 Tube Guitar Combo Amp26 watt
